"'''An Uneasy Peace'''" was an interactive adventure associated with the [[Eye of the Sun trilogy]] for the [[Living Force (roleplaying campaign)|Living Force]] campaign. It ran one time only, at the [[Winter Fantasy 2001|Winter Fantasy]] convention in [[January]] [[2001]]. It was written by [[Jae Walker]] with assistance from [[Morrie Mullins (real person)|Morrie Mullins]].

==Plot summary==
After the illegal actions of [[Velin Wir]] were proven and his [[Metatheran Cartel jungle base|jungle base]] destroyed by his own [[Metatheran Cartel]], a grand celebration was held in [[Gadrin]], similar to the one that Wir had interrupted a little over a month before. During the celebration, [[Governor/Legends|Governor]] [[Barnab Chistor]] decided to let the people have their say in whether the Cartel would be allowed to remain on the planet, holding a vote that was to be carried out using [[Datapad/Legends|datapads]]. Certain people circulated through the crowds, offering to buy the datapads for 5,000 [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]] each.

Many of the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Padawan/Legends|Padawans]] attending the celebration abstained from the vote, though many had thought the Jedi were going to vote as a bloc. When the votes were counted, the results were a tie, so Governor Chistor threw the deciding vote and denied the Cartel the opportunity to reestablish offices on [[Cularin/Legends|Cularin's]] surface.

As a gesture of good faith, the Cartel donated a [[Warship/Legends|warship]], the ''[[XP-38]]'', to the people of Cularin for their defense. During the course of tours being provided to the celebration attendants, there were several attempts to hijack the ship, but the heroic citizens of Cularin were able to foil those efforts.

